Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with understanding joint attention in social scene videos using saliency maps and convolutional attention mechanisms. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes an end-to-end learning method for joint attention estimation. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses novel attention mechanisms to improve joint attention localization. 
4. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a potential category as joint attention has applications in this field. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also possible as the paper deals with analyzing social scene videos.
